21 * and Realtek Echo Protocol (RRCP-REP) packets.

24#include <sys/cdefs.h>
25#ifndef lint
26__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-rrcp.c,v 1.6 2017/02/05 04:05:05 spz Exp $");
27#endif
28
29/* \summary: Realtek Remote Control Protocol (RRCP) printer */
30
31#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
32#include "config.h"
33#endif
34
35#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
36
37#include "netdissect.h"
38#include "addrtoname.h"
39#include "extract.h"
40#include "ether.h"
41
42#define RRCP_OPCODE_MASK 0x7F /* 0x00 = hello, 0x01 = get, 0x02 = set */
43#define RRCP_ISREPLY 0x80 /* 0 = request to switch, 0x80 = reply from switch */
44
45#define RRCP_PROTO_OFFSET 0 /* proto - 1 byte, must be 1 */
46#define RRCP_OPCODE_ISREPLY_OFFSET 1 /* opcode and isreply flag - 1 byte */
47#define RRCP_AUTHKEY_OFFSET 2 /* authorization key - 2 bytes, 0x2379 by default */
48
49/* most packets */
50#define RRCP_REG_ADDR_OFFSET 4 /* register address - 2 bytes */
51#define RRCP_REG_DATA_OFFSET 6 /* register data - 4 bytes */
52#define RRCP_COOKIE1_OFFSET 10 /* 4 bytes */
53#define RRCP_COOKIE2_OFFSET 14 /* 4 bytes */
54
55/* hello reply packets */
56#define RRCP_DOWNLINK_PORT_OFFSET 4 /* 1 byte */
57#define RRCP_UPLINK_PORT_OFFSET 5 /* 1 byte */
58#define RRCP_UPLINK_MAC_OFFSET 6 /* 6 byte MAC address */
59#define RRCP_CHIP_ID_OFFSET 12 /* 2 bytes */
60#define RRCP_VENDOR_ID_OFFSET 14 /* 4 bytes */
61
62static const struct tok proto_values[] = {
63 { 1, "RRCP" },
64 { 2, "RRCP-REP" },
65 { 0, NULL }
66};
67
68static const struct tok opcode_values[] = {
69 { 0, "hello" },
70 { 1, "get" },
71 { 2, "set" },
72 { 0, NULL }
73};
74
75/*
76 * Print RRCP requests
77 */
78void
79rrcp_print(netdissect_options *ndo,
80 register const u_char *cp,
81 u_int length _U_,
82 const struct lladdr_info *src,
83 const struct lladdr_info *dst)
84{
85 uint8_t rrcp_proto;
86 uint8_t rrcp_opcode;
87
88 ND_TCHECK(*(cp + RRCP_PROTO_OFFSET));
89 rrcp_proto = *(cp + RRCP_PROTO_OFFSET);
90 ND_TCHECK(*(cp + RRCP_OPCODE_ISREPLY_OFFSET));
91 rrcp_opcode = (*(cp + RRCP_OPCODE_ISREPLY_OFFSET)) & RRCP_OPCODE_MASK;
92 if (src != NULL && dst != NULL) {
93 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s > %s, ",
94 (src->addr_string)(ndo, src->addr),
95 (dst->addr_string)(ndo, dst->addr)));
96 }
97 ND_PRINT((ndo, "%s %s",
98 tok2str(proto_values,"RRCP-0x%02x",rrcp_proto),
99 ((*(cp + RRCP_OPCODE_ISREPLY_OFFSET)) & RRCP_ISREPLY) ? "reply" : "query"));
100 if (rrcp_proto==1){
101 ND_PRINT((ndo, ": %s",
102 tok2str(opcode_values,"unknown opcode (0x%02x)",rrcp_opcode)));
103 }
104 if (rrcp_opcode==1 || rrcp_opcode==2){
105 ND_TCHECK2(*(cp + RRCP_REG_ADDR_OFFSET), 6);
106 ND_PRINT((ndo, " addr=0x%04x, data=0x%08x",
107 EXTRACT_LE_16BITS(cp + RRCP_REG_ADDR_OFFSET),
108 EXTRACT_LE_32BITS(cp + RRCP_REG_DATA_OFFSET)));
109 }
110 if (rrcp_proto==1){
111 ND_TCHECK2(*(cp + RRCP_AUTHKEY_OFFSET), 2);
112 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", auth=0x%04x",
113 EXTRACT_16BITS(cp + RRCP_AUTHKEY_OFFSET)));
114 }
115 if (rrcp_proto==1 && rrcp_opcode==0 &&
116 ((*(cp + RRCP_OPCODE_ISREPLY_OFFSET)) & RRCP_ISREPLY)){
117 ND_TCHECK2(*(cp + RRCP_VENDOR_ID_OFFSET), 4);
118 ND_PRINT((ndo, " downlink_port=%d, uplink_port=%d, uplink_mac=%s, vendor_id=%08x ,chip_id=%04x ",
119 *(cp + RRCP_DOWNLINK_PORT_OFFSET),
120 *(cp + RRCP_UPLINK_PORT_OFFSET),
121 etheraddr_string(ndo, cp + RRCP_UPLINK_MAC_OFFSET),
122 EXTRACT_32BITS(cp + RRCP_VENDOR_ID_OFFSET),
123 EXTRACT_16BITS(cp + RRCP_CHIP_ID_OFFSET)));
124 }else if (rrcp_opcode==1 || rrcp_opcode==2 || rrcp_proto==2){
125 ND_TCHECK2(*(cp + RRCP_COOKIE2_OFFSET), 4);
126 ND_PRINT((ndo, ", cookie=0x%08x%08x ",
127 EXTRACT_32BITS(cp + RRCP_COOKIE2_OFFSET),
128 EXTRACT_32BITS(cp + RRCP_COOKIE1_OFFSET)));
129 }
130 return;
131
132trunc:
133 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|rrcp]"));
134}
